# Fluff Date: 2026-02-28 17:47:08
overview:<p>The Ares is a 135-ton superheavy tripod OmniMech developed in 3136 as part of the Republic of the Sphere's secretive Rhodes Project. Conceived by Rhodes Foundry on Devil's Rock as the heavier sister design to the Poseidon, the Ares was designed to provide the Republic's defenders with a flexible, reconfigurable superheavy combat platform capable of engaging threats across all range bands. The design incorporated OmniMech technology to ease maintenance and enable rapid battlefield reconfiguration, critical advantages for a machine operating under wartime conditions with limited logistical support.</p><p>Requiring a three-person crew of pilot, gunner, and technician, the Ares was deliberately built to visually resemble the Poseidon, a choice that has repeatedly confused enemy intelligence services into misidentifying its configurations as entirely separate chassis designs. Production has since expanded beyond the Republic, with new manufacturing established in the Free Worlds League following the fall of Terra.</p>

capabilities:<p>Built on a Rhodes-M Endo-Composite frame powered by a PlasmaStar 270 fusion engine, the Ares reaches a maximum speed of just 32 kilometers per hour, making it one of the slowest BattleMechs in active service. What it sacrifices in mobility it compensates for with 28.5 tons of Maximillian 320 standard armor protected by CASE II, giving it exceptional survivability against sustained fire. The tripod configuration provides enhanced stability and allows the Ares to change direction without reducing speed, a meaningful tactical advantage for a design that cannot afford to waste momentum.</p><p>The Ares carries 41 tons of pod space, enabling a vast array of possible configurations. Every Ares mounts a fixed weapon suite across its torso and legs: paired Clan-grade extended-range medium lasers, three extended-range small lasers, dual LRM-5 and triple SRM-2 launchers, and six anti-personnel pods for infantry defense. This fixed armament ensures a baseline combat capability regardless of configuration.</p><p>In its primary Zeus configuration, the design pairs twin Clan ER PPCs with three Streak SRM-6 launchers and a targeting computer, creating a versatile combatant effective at multiple engagement ranges. The three-person cockpit allows simultaneous weapons management, navigation, and damage control, while also enabling the Ares to function as a command platform coordinating allied forces.</p>

deployment:<p>This configuration centers on an Improved Heavy Gauss Rifle mounted in the right arm with six tons of ammunition, delivering devastating single-shot firepower at extreme range. Three additional Clan extended-range medium lasers in the left arm provide supplementary fire, while CASE II protects against catastrophic ammunition explosions. Seven additional double heat sinks round out the configuration, making it a relatively cool-running but hard-hitting assault platform well suited to siege operations and defensive positions where the Ares' slow speed is less of a liability.</p>

history:<p>The Ares emerged from the Republic of the Sphere's Rhodes Project, a desperate effort to develop decisive weapons platforms as the Republic crumbled following Gray Monday. Development began in approximately 3135, shortly after the Poseidon completed its prototype trials, with Rhodes Foundry on Devil's Rock tasked with producing a heavier, more flexible companion design. The Ares entered service in 3136 and was initially deployed in strict secrecy with Stone's Brigades and garrison units on Devil's Rock.</p><p>Throughout the early 3140s, Ares tripods were deployed on covert reconnaissance and raiding missions along the Republic's borders, their enormous size notwithstanding. Republic commanders used the 'Mechs to intimidate neighboring states and deter potential aggressors, with the deliberate confusion surrounding the Ares' configurations multiplying its perceived numbers. By 3145, Devil's Rock had become a frontline world threatened by Clan Wolf expansion, prompting plans to duplicate production on Mars within the Terran system. Rhodes Foundry's facilities were rigged with demolition charges as a contingency against capture.</p><p>The Ares saw its most significant combat during the Battle of Terra in 3151, where Republic forces deployed the design extensively during Operation Four Horsemen against Clan Wolf. The superheavy tripods initially proved devastating, forcing Wolf warriors to retreat on several occasions, but the Clans eventually adapted their tactics and systematically brought down the Republic's colossals. During Terra's conquest, Clan Wolf salvaged several Ares frames, repairing and crewing them with bondsmen from the former Republic Armed Forces for use in the ilClan Trial against Clan Jade Falcon.</p><p>Following the Trial, Wolf's Dragoons recovered additional Ares units from the battlefield, studying and disassembling some to reverse-engineer the design. Colonel Henry Kincaid transferred six functional units along with supporting technical data to Captain-General Nikol Marik of the Free Worlds League. The League subsequently fielded a full company of Ares with the First Free Worlds Guards on Marik, with newly manufactured units indicating the League had become the first Inner Sphere state to independently produce the design since the Republic's fall.</p><p>Julian Davion's Dawn Guards similarly received Ares units as a gift from Devlin Stone, deploying at least a lance during Operation DAWN and developing the Apollo configuration to suit Federated Suns doctrine. On Yorii in 3151, a three-sided battle between Fidelis survivors, Capellan forces, and mercenaries apparently working for Clan Sea Fox highlighted the intense competition to acquire and replicate the superheavy tripod design across the Inner Sphere.</p>

